The Social Democratic Party (SDP) yesterday declared that Nigerians have the option of not choosing between the All Progressives Congress (APC) and the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in 2023, adding that its platform is a viable platform having won national elections in the past. This comes as the party ratified the position of their national chairman, Dr Olu Ogunleye, during its National Executive Committee (NEC) meeting attended by four presidential aspirants ahead of the 2023 election. The presidential aspirants that attended the NEC meeting monitored by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) are: Chief Femi Olufunmiladi; Mrs Dorathy Nuhu – Aken’ova; Prince Adewole Adebayo and Dr Folorunso Daudu. LEADERSHIP reports that the SDP 2019 presidential running mate, Shehu Gabam, had raised a motion to ratify the acting national chairmanship of Ogunleye as well as the national publicity secretary, Amb Rufus B Aigenigba and national speaker, Youth Parliament, Hon China Uchechukwu. The motion was supported by the SDP chairman, Akwa Ibom State, Engr Willington Odiong and the leaders emerged through voice votes. Speaking during his opening speech, the SDP national chairman, Ogunleye said the party is the best alternative for Nigerians adding that they will win the 2023 presidential election. Ogunleye who thanked all the NEC and NWC members for the endorsement, said it is now a new hope for the party. According to Ogunleye, SDP won the presidential election in 1993, adding that it is exactly 30 years, hoping that history will repeat itself in 2023. “The country is in total collapse but the SDP is bringing hope and assurance. We are providing Nigeria with an alternative platform. You don’t have to take the choice of the two devils. “SDP is here to rescue Nigeria. SDP will win the 2023 General election. SDP will win the Ekiti Governorship Election with Segun Oni,” Ogunleye added. 